  "body": "---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIn [truffle doc](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/reference/configuration), it has the following statement for default network gas: \r\n\r\n> gas: Gas limit used for deploys. Default is 4712388.\r\n\r\nHowever, it is updated to 6721975 in [This gas update commit](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/commit/0baeedd4741a484a39c2474f294c216eff88d9a1).\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nI was deploying contract to ganache with gas limit of 6200000 and found this. The deployer is trying to send transaction with higher gas of our limit on ganache.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe doc should change the stated value to new one.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"Migrations\" exceeded the block limit (with a gas value you set).\r\n   * Block limit:  0x20175c8\r\n   * Gas sent:     6721975\r\n   * Try:\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: mac\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.0.21\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v9.2.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.9.0",
